The paper presents a deep learning approach for drug-target interaction prediction, which involves feature manipulation and classification using convolutional neural networks. This work involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques, which are commonly associated with the cs.LG and cs.AI sub-categories. Additionally, the use of evolutionary and structural features suggests a potential association with the cs.CE and cs.DB sub-categories. Finally, the use of neural networks for classification suggests a potential association with the cs.NE sub-category.
